---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - SkibidiMusic">
    <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 md:py-16 max-w-3xl">
        <h1
            class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-400 to-pink-600"
        >
            Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: November 23, 2025</p>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    1. Introduction
                </h2>
                <p>
                    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong class="text-white"
                        >SkibidiMusic Bot</strong
                    > ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your information
                    when you use our Discord bot. We are committed to protecting
                    your privacy.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    2. Information Processed
                </h2>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    To function, the Bot temporarily processes the following
                    data:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2 mb-4">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Discord User ID:</strong> To know who requested a
                        song.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Discord Server (Guild) ID:</strong> To manage the
                        music queue for your specific server.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Voice Channel ID:</strong> To join the correct voice
                        channel.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p
                    class="mb-4 bg-purple-900/30 p-4 rounded-lg border border-purple-500/30"
                >
                    <strong class="text-purple-300">Important:</strong> This data
                    is <strong class="text-white">NOT stored</strong> in any database
                    or file. It exists only in the Bot's memory while it is running
                    and is lost when the Bot restarts.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-2">We do <strong>NOT</strong> collect or store:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2">
                    <li>Personal messages (DMs).</li>
                    <li>Voice conversations.</li>
                    <li>Personal identifiable information (PII).</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    3. How We Use Your Information
                </h2>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    We use the collected information solely for the purpose of:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2">
                    <li>Providing the music playback service.</li>
                    <li>Managing queues and playlists.</li>
                    <li>Enforcing our Terms of Service.</li>
                    <li>Troubleshooting technical issues.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    4. Data Sharing
                </h2>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal identification
                    information to others.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We may interact with third-party services (YouTube, Spotify,
                    Deezer) to retrieve music content. These services may
                    collect data in accordance with their own privacy policies
                    when content is requested.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    5. Data Retention
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Data such as the current music queue is stored temporarily
                    in memory and is cleared when the Bot restarts or when the
                    queue is cleared. We do not maintain a persistent database
                    of user activity history.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    6. Your Rights
                </h2>
                <p>
                    You may request the deletion of any data we may have stored
                    about you (if any) by contacting us. However, since we
                    primarily store transient data necessary for the Bot's
                    immediate function, simply stopping use of the Bot will
                    effectively cease data collection.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    7. Changes to This Policy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will
                    notify users of any significant changes by updating the
                    "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                    8. Contact
                </h2>
                <p>
                    If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact
                    the developer via the <a
                        href="https://github.com/AngeloAL12/SkibidiMusic"
                        class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline"
                        >GitHub repository</a
                    >.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
